      "content": "It takes immense courage to admit that carrying others' expectations feels so heavy and hollow right now. When the person inside feels erased to satisfy the \"mask\" others expect, the exhaustion can feel absolutely isolating and unbearable. Many people experience this deep disconnect where the performance of \"being okay\" leaves no room for the tired reality underneath. Please keep reaching out, even if it feels like there's no \"real\" person left to benefit from it; acknowledging that this specific weight is crushing is the first step toward finding relief.",
